SIMPLE: supernaturalism
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supernaturalism
<hw>Su`per*nat"u*ral*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being supernatural; supernaturalness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>The doctrine of a divine and supernatural agency in the production of the miracles and revelations recorded in the Bible, and in the grace which renews and sanctifies men, -- in opposition to the doctrine which denies the agency of any other than physical or natural causes in the case.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>supranaturalism</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supernaturalist</ent>⟦br⟧
